  24. ‌let rec_flag ppf = function
  25.   | Nonrecursive -> ()
  26.   | Recursive -> fprintf ppf " rec"

  28. ‌let machtype_component ppf = function
  29.   | Val -> fprintf ppf "val"
  30.   | Addr -> fprintf ppf "addr"
  31.   | Int -> fprintf ppf "int"
  32.   | Float -> fprintf ppf "float"

  34. ‌let machtype ppf mty =
  35.   match Array.length mty with
  36.   | 0 -> fprintf ppf "unit"
  37.   | n -> machtype_component ppf mty.(0);
  38.          for i = 1 to n-1 do
  39.            fprintf ppf "*%a" machtype_component mty.(i)
  40.          done

  42. ‌let exttype ppf = function
  43.   | XInt -> fprintf ppf "int"
  44.   | XInt32 -> fprintf ppf "int32"
  45.   | XInt64 -> fprintf ppf "int64"
  46.   | XFloat -> fprintf ppf "float"

  48. ‌let extcall_signature ppf (ty_res, ty_args) =
  49.   begin match ty_args with
  50.   | [] -> ()
  51.   | ty_arg1 :: ty_args ->
  52.       exttype ppf ty_arg1;
  53.       List.iter (fun ty -> fprintf ppf ",%a" exttype ty) ty_args
  54.   end;
  55.   fprintf ppf "->%a" machtype ty_res

  57. let integer_comparison = function
  58.   | Ceq -> "=="
  59.   | Cne -> "!="
  60.   | Clt -> "<"
  61.   | Cle -> "<="
  62.   | Cgt -> ">"
  63.   | Cge -> ">="

  65. ‌let float_comparison = function
  66.   | CFeq -> "=="
  67.   | CFneq -> "!="
  68.   | CFlt -> "<"
  69.   | CFnlt -> "!<"
  70.   | CFle -> "<="
  71.   | CFnle -> "!<="
  72.   | CFgt -> ">"
  73.   | CFngt -> "!>"
  74.   | CFge -> ">="
  75.   | CFnge -> "!>="

  78.   | Byte_unsigned -> "unsigned int8"

  89. ‌let phantom_defining_expr ppf defining_expr =
  90.   match defining_expr with
  91.   | Cphantom_const_int i -> Targetint.print ppf i
  92.   | Cphantom_const_symbol sym -> Format.pp_print_string ppf sym
  93.   | Cphantom_var var -> V.print ppf var
  94.   | Cphantom_offset_var { var; offset_in_words; } ->
  95.     Format.fprintf ppf "%a+(%d)" V.print var offset_in_words
  96.   | Cphantom_read_field { var; field; } ->
  97.     Format.fprintf ppf "%a[%d]" V.print var field
  98.   | Cphantom_read_symbol_field { sym; field; } ->
  99.     Format.fprintf ppf "%s[%d]" sym field
  100.   | Cphantom_block { tag; fields; } ->
  101.     Format.fprintf ppf "[%d: " tag;
  102.     List.iter (fun field ->
  103.         Format.fprintf ppf "%a; " V.print field)
  104.       fields;
  105.     Format.fprintf ppf "]"

  107. let phantom_defining_expr_opt ppf defining_expr =
  108.   match defining_expr with
  109.   | None -> Format.pp_print_string ppf "()"
  110.   | Some defining_expr -> phantom_defining_expr ppf defining_expr

  112. ‌let location d =
  113.   if not !Clflags.locations then ""
  114.   else Debuginfo.to_string d

  116. ‌let operation d = function
  117.   | Capply _ty -> "app" ^ location d
  118.   | Cextcall(lbl, _ty_res, _ty_args, _alloc) ->
  119.       Printf.sprintf "extcall \"%s\"%s" lbl (location d)
  120.   | Cload {memory_chunk; mutability} -> (
  121.     match mutability with
  122.     | Asttypes.Immutable -> Printf.sprintf "load %s" (chunk memory_chunk)
  123.     | Asttypes.Mutable   -> Printf.sprintf "load_mut %s" (chunk memory_chunk))
  124.   | Calloc -> "alloc" ^ location d
  125.   | Cstore (c, init) ->
  126.     let init =
  127.       match init with
  128.       | Lambda.Heap_initialization -> "(heap-init)"
  129.       | Lambda.Root_initialization -> "(root-init)"
  130.       | Lambda.Assignment -> ""
  131.     in
  132.     Printf.sprintf "store %s%s" (chunk c) init
  133.   | Caddi -> "+"
  134.   | Csubi -> "-"
  135.   | Cmuli -> "*"
  136.   | Cmulhi -> "*h"
  137.   | Cdivi -> "/"
  138.   | Cmodi -> "mod"
  139.   | Cand -> "and"
  140.   | Cor -> "or"
  141.   | Cxor -> "xor"
  142.   | Clsl -> "<<"
  143.   | Clsr -> ">>u"
  144.   | Casr -> ">>s"
  145.   | Ccmpi c -> integer_comparison c
  146.   | Caddv -> "+v"
  147.   | Cadda -> "+a"
  148.   | Ccmpa c -> Printf.sprintf "%sa" (integer_comparison c)
  149.   | Cnegf -> "~f"
  150.   | Cabsf -> "absf"
  151.   | Caddf -> "+f"
  152.   | Csubf -> "-f"
  153.   | Cmulf -> "*f"
  154.   | Cdivf -> "/f"
  155.   | Cfloatofint -> "floatofint"
  156.   | Cintoffloat -> "intoffloat"
  157.   | Ccmpf c -> Printf.sprintf "%sf" (float_comparison c)
  158.   | Craise k -> Lambda.raise_kind k ^ location d
  159.   | Ccheckbound -> "checkbound" ^ location d
  160.   | Copaque -> "opaque"
  161.   | Cdls_get -> "dls_get"

  163. ‌let rec expr ppf = function
  164.   | Cconst_int (n, _dbg) -> fprintf ppf "%i" n
  165.   | Cconst_natint (n, _dbg) ->
  166.     fprintf ppf "%s" (Nativeint.to_string n)
  167.   | Cconst_float (n, _dbg) -> fprintf ppf "%F" n
  168.   | Cconst_symbol (s, _dbg) -> fprintf ppf "\"%s\"" s
  169.   | Cvar id -> V.print ppf id
  170.   | Clet(id, def, (Clet(_, _, _) as body)) ->
  171.       let print_binding id ppf def =
  172.         fprintf ppf "@[<2>%a@ %a@]"
  173.           VP.print id expr def in
  174.       let rec in_part ppf = function
  175.         | Clet(id, def, body) ->
  176.             fprintf ppf "@ %a" (print_binding id) def;
  177.             in_part ppf body
  178.         | exp -> exp in
  179.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(let@ @[<1>(%a" (print_binding id) def;
  180.       let exp = in_part ppf body in
  181.       fprintf ppf ")@]@ %a)@]" sequence exp
  182.   | Clet(id, def, body) ->
  183.      fprintf ppf
  184.       "@[<2>(let@ @[<2>%a@ %a@]@ %a)@]"
  185.       VP.print id expr def sequence body
  186.   | Clet_mut(id, kind, def, body) ->
  187.     fprintf ppf
  188.       "@[<2>(let_mut@ @[<2>%a: %a@ %a@]@ %a)@]"
  189.       VP.print id machtype kind expr def sequence body
  190.   | Cphantom_let(var, def, (Cphantom_let(_, _, _) as body)) ->
  191.       let print_binding var ppf def =
  192.         fprintf ppf "@[<2>%a@ %a@]" VP.print var
  193.           phantom_defining_expr_opt def
  194.       in
  195.       let rec in_part ppf = function
  196.         | Cphantom_let(var, def, body) ->
  197.             fprintf ppf "@ %a" (print_binding var) def;
  198.             in_part ppf body
  199.         | exp -> exp in
  200.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(let?@ @[<1>(%a" (print_binding var) def;
  201.       let exp = in_part ppf body in
  202.       fprintf ppf ")@]@ %a)@]" sequence exp
  203.   | Cphantom_let(var, def, body) ->
  204.     fprintf ppf
  205.       "@[<2>(let?@ @[<2>%a@ %a@]@ %a)@]"
  206.       VP.print var
  207.       phantom_defining_expr_opt def
  208.       sequence body
  209.   | Cassign(id, exp) ->
  210.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(assign @[<2>%a@ %a@])@]" V.print id expr exp
  211.   | Ctuple el ->
  212.       let tuple ppf el =
  213.        let first = ref true in
  214.        List.iter
  215.         (fun e ->
  216.           if !first then first := false else fprintf ppf "@ ";
  217.           expr ppf e)
  218.         el in
  219.       fprintf ppf "@[<1>[%a]@]" tuple el
  220.   | Cop(op, el, dbg) ->
  221.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(%s" (operation dbg op);
  222.       List.iter (fun e -> fprintf ppf "@ %a" expr e) el;
  223.       begin match op with
  224.       | Capply mty -> fprintf ppf "@ %a" machtype mty
  225.       | Cextcall(_, ty_res, ty_args, _) ->
  226.           fprintf ppf "@ %a" extcall_signature (ty_res, ty_args)
  227.       | _ -> ()
  228.       end;
  229.       fprintf ppf ")@]"
  230.   | Csequence(e1, e2) ->
  231.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(seq@ %a@ %a)@]" sequence e1 sequence e2
  232.   | Cifthenelse(e1, _e2_dbg, e2, _e3_dbg, e3, _dbg) ->
  233.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(if@ %a@ %a@ %a)@]" expr e1 expr e2 expr e3
  234.   | Cswitch(e1, index, cases, _dbg) ->
  235. ‌      let print_case i ppf =
  236.         for j = 0 to Array.length index - 1 do
  237.           if index.(j) = i then fprintf ppf "case %i:" j
  238.         done in
  239. ‌      let print_cases ppf =
  240.        for i = 0 to Array.length cases - 1 do
  241.         fprintf ppf "@ @[<2>%t@ %a@]" (print_case i) sequence (fst cases.(i))
  242.        done in
  243.       fprintf ppf "@[<v 0>@[<2>(switch@ %a@ @]%t)@]" expr e1 print_cases
  244.   | Ccatch(flag, handlers, e1) ->
  245. ‌      let print_handler ppf (i, ids, e2, _dbg) =
  246.         fprintf ppf "(%d%a)@ %a"
  247.           i
  248.           (fun ppf ids ->
  249.              List.iter
  250.                (fun (id, ty) ->
  251.                  fprintf ppf "@ %a: %a"
  252.                    VP.print id machtype ty)
  253.                ids) ids
  254.           sequence e2
  255.       in
  256. ‌      let print_handlers ppf l =
  257.         List.iter (print_handler ppf) l
  258.       in
  259.       fprintf ppf
  260.         "@[<2>(catch%a@ %a@;<1 -2>with%a)@]"
  261.         rec_flag flag
  262.         sequence e1
  263.         print_handlers handlers
  264.   | Cexit (i, el) ->
  265.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(exit %d" i;
  266.       List.iter (fun e -> fprintf ppf "@ %a" expr e) el;
  267.       fprintf ppf ")@]"
  268.   | Ctrywith(e1, id, e2, _dbg) ->
  269.       fprintf ppf "@[<2>(try@ %a@;<1 -2>with@ %a@ %a)@]"
  270.              sequence e1 VP.print id sequence e2

  272. ‌and sequence ppf = function
  273.   | Csequence(e1, e2) -> fprintf ppf "%a@ %a" sequence e1 sequence e2
  274.   | e -> expression ppf e

  276. and expression ppf e = fprintf ppf "%a" expr e

  278. ‌let fundecl ppf f =
  279.   let print_cases ppf cases =
  280.     let first = ref true in
  281.     List.iter
  282.      (fun (id, ty) ->
  283.        if !first then first := false else fprintf ppf "@ ";
  284.        fprintf ppf "%a: %a" VP.print id machtype ty)
  285.      cases in
  286.   fprintf ppf "@[<1>(function%s %s@;<1 4>@[<1>(%a)@]@ @[%a@])@]@."
  287.          (location f.fun_dbg) f.fun_name
  288.          print_cases f.fun_args sequence f.fun_body

  290. ‌let data_item ppf = function
  291.   | Cdefine_symbol s -> fprintf ppf "\"%s\":" s
  292.   | Cglobal_symbol s -> fprintf ppf "global \"%s\"" s
  293.   | Cint8 n -> fprintf ppf "byte %i" n
  294.   | Cint16 n -> fprintf ppf "int16 %i" n
  295.   | Cint32 n -> fprintf ppf "int32 %s" (Nativeint.to_string n)
  296.   | Cint n -> fprintf ppf "int %s" (Nativeint.to_string n)
  297.   | Csingle f -> fprintf ppf "single %F" f
  298.   | Cdouble f -> fprintf ppf "double %F" f
  299.   | Csymbol_address s -> fprintf ppf "addr \"%s\"" s
  300.   | Cstring s -> fprintf ppf "string \"%s\"" s
  301.   | Cskip n -> fprintf ppf "skip %i" n
  302.   | Calign n -> fprintf ppf "align %i" n

  304. ‌let data ppf dl =
